    <h2>
        About Virtual Classes
    </h2>
    <p style="margin: 0.4em 0px 0.5em; line-height: 19px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); ">
        Virtual education is a term describing online education using the Internet. This 
        term is used in K-12 schooling, often to refer to<span 
            class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a class="mw-redirect" 
            href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyber_school" 
            style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" 
            title="Cyber school">cyber schools</a>, and in higher education, where 
        so-called<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a class="mw-redirect" 
            href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtual_Universities" 
            style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" 
            title="Virtual Universities">Virtual Universities</a><span 
            class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>have been established. A virtual 
        program (or a virtual course of studies) is a study program in which all 
        courses, or at least a significant portion of the courses, are virtual courses, 
        whether in<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a class="mw-redirect" 
            href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Synchronous" 
            style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" 
            title="Synchronous">synchronous</a><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>(i.e. 
        real time) or<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a class="mw-redirect" 
            href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asynchronous" 
            style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" 
            title="Asynchronous">asynchronous</a><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>(i.e. 
        self-paced) formats.</p>
<p style="margin: 0.4em 0px 0.5em; line-height: 19px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); ">
    Virtual courses&nbsp;– a synonym is online courses&nbsp;– are courses delivered on the 
    Internet. &quot;Virtual&quot; is used here to characterize the fact that the course is not 
    taught in a classroom face-to-face but through some substitute mode that can be 
    associated with classroom teaching. That means people do not have to go to the 
    real class to learn.</p>
<p style="margin: 0.4em 0px 0.5em; line-height: 19px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); ">
    Both the asynchronous and synchronous methods rely heavily on self-motivation, 
    self-discipline, and ability for effective written communication.<sup 
        id="cite_ref-1" class="reference" 
        style="line-height: 1em; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; "><a 
        href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtual_education#cite_note-1" 
        style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; white-space: nowrap; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p style="margin: 0.4em 0px 0.5em; line-height: 19px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); ">
    Although there is a long and varied history of<span 
        class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a 
        href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Distance_education" 
        style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" 
        title="Distance education">distance education</a>, the current intersection 
    of technology as a means to facilitate real-time communication with 
    community-centered interaction, and the increasing acceptance and employment of 
    those developments in the broader culture, have positioned<span 
        class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a 
        href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtual_school" 
        style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" 
        title="Virtual school">virtual schools</a><span 
        class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>in a position of significant 
    innovation and responsibility. In an educational environment in which school 
    choice for families and students is valued, “cyber<span 
        class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a 
        href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charter_school" 
        style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" 
        title="Charter school">charter schools</a>, as an outgrowth of the charter 
    movement and the virtual school movement, represent a unique group of schools 
    characterized by both their administrative model and their course delivery 
    technology</p>
    <p style="margin: 0.4em 0px 0.5em; line-height: 19px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); ">
        Many virtual study programs are mainly text based, using<span 
            class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a 
            href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML" 
            style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" 
            title="HTML">HTML</a>,<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a 
            class="mw-redirect" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PowerPoint" 
            style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" 
            title="PowerPoint">PowerPoint</a>, or<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a 
            class="mw-redirect" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PDF" 
            style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" 
            title="PDF">PDF</a><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>documents. 
        Any attempt to personalize the educational experience is essential in that 
        students respond to personal attention and feedback. Today a wide spectrum of 
        instruction modes is available, including the following:</p>
    <ul style="line-height: 19px; list-style-type: square; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: url(data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAUAAAANAQMAAABb8jbLAAAABlBMVEX///8AUow5QSOjAAAAAXRSTlMAQObYZgAAABpJREFUeF5VxaEBAAAAgjBO9nyjGoUwPuFdCRqSA8lTAUBSAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em; "><i>Virtual Classroom:</i><span 
                class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>Live teacher instruction and feedback 
            online that enables real-time voice interaction, whiteboard sharing, and 
            breakout sessions to enhance a student&#39;s learning experience. This provides 
            students an opportunity to interact with the teacher as well as classmates by 
            oral and written communication.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em; "><i>Virtual operating room:</i><span 
                class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>giving students a space to learn the 
            basic induction procedure before stepping foot in the real-life operating room.<sup 
                id="cite_ref-3" class="reference" 
                style="line-height: 1em; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; "><a 
                href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtual_education#cite_note-3" 
                style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; white-space: nowrap; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em; "><i>Hypertext courses:</i><span 
                class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>Structured course material is used as 
            in a conventional distance education program. However, all material is provided 
            electronically and can be viewed with a browser. Hyperlinks connect text, 
            multimedia parts and exercises.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em; "><i>Video-based courses</i><span 
                class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>are like face-to-face classroom 
            courses, with a lecturer speaking and Powerpoint slides or online examples used 
            for illustration. Video-streaming technologies is used. Students watch the video 
            by means of freeware or plug-ins.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em; "><i>Audio-based courses</i><span 
                class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>are similar but instead of moving 
            pictures only the sound track of the lecturer is provided. Often the course 
            pages are enhanced with a text transcription of the lecture.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em; "><i>Animated courses:</i><span 
                class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>Enriching text-oriented or audio-based 
            course material by animations is generally a good way of making the content and 
            its appearance more interesting. Animations are created using<span 
                class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a class="mw-redirect" 
                href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Macromedia_Flash" 
                style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" 
                title="Macromedia Flash">Macromedia Flash</a><span 
                class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>or similar technologies.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em; "><i>Web-supported textbook courses</i><span 
                class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>are based on specific textbooks. 
            Students read and reflect on the chapters by themselves. Review questions, 
            topics for discussion, exercises, case studies, etc. are given chapterwise on a 
            website and discussed with the lecturer. Class meetings may be held to discuss 
            matters in a chatroom, for example.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference" 
                style="line-height: 1em; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; "><a 
                href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtual_education#cite_note-4" 
                style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; white-space: nowrap; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em; "><i>Peer-to-peer courses</i><span 
                class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>are courses taught &quot;on-demand&quot; and 
            without a prepared curriculum. A new field of online education has emerged in 
            2007 through new online education platforms.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em; "><i>Social Networking:</i><span 
                class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>Using Web 2.0 technologies in virtual 
            classrooms promotes increased social interaction, student-centered instruction 
            and a problem solving curriculum. Students can address a problem that is 
            oriented to a cross curriculum activity. Teachers will act as guides and 
            resources, but it is up to the students to collaborate, discuss, review ideas, 
            and present solutions.</li>
    </ul>
